  "root_text": {
    "sn3.17:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 3.17 ",
    "sn3.17:0.2": "2. Dutiyavagga ",
    "sn3.17:0.3": "Appamādasutta ",
    "sn3.17:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn3.17:1.2": "Ekamantaṁ nisīdi. ",
    "sn3.17:1.3": "Ekamantaṁ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn3.17:1.4": "“atthi nu kho, bhante, eko dhammo yo ubho atthe samadhiggayha tiṭṭhati—",
    "sn3.17:1.5": "diṭṭhadhammikañceva atthaṁ samparāyikañcā”ti? ",
    "sn3.17:2.1": "“Atthi kho, mahārāja, eko dhammo yo ubho atthe samadhiggayha tiṭṭhati—",
    "sn3.17:2.2": "diṭṭhadhammikañceva atthaṁ samparāyikañcā”ti. ",
    "sn3.17:3.1": "“Katamo pana, bhante, eko dhammo, yo ubho atthe samadhiggayha tiṭṭhati—",
    "sn3.17:3.2": "diṭṭhadhammikañceva atthaṁ samparāyikañcā”ti? ",
    "sn3.17:4.1": "“Appamādo kho, mahārāja, eko dhammo, yo ubho atthe samadhiggayha tiṭṭhati—",
    "sn3.17:4.2": "diṭṭhadhammikañceva atthaṁ samparāyikañcāti. ",
    "sn3.17:4.3": "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṁ pāṇānaṁ padajātāni, sabbāni tāni hatthipade samodhānaṁ gacchanti, hatthipadaṁ tesaṁ aggamakkhāyati—yadidaṁ mahantattena; ",
    "sn3.17:4.4": "evameva kho, mahārāja, appamādo eko dhammo, yo ubho atthe samadhiggayha tiṭṭhati—",
    "sn3.17:4.5": "diṭṭhadhammikañceva atthaṁ samparāyikañcā”ti. ",
    "sn3.17:4.6": "Idamavoca …pe… ",
    "sn3.17:5.1": "“Āyuṁ arogiyaṁ vaṇṇaṁ, ",
    "sn3.17:5.2": "saggaṁ uccākulīnataṁ; ",
    "sn3.17:5.3": "Ratiyo patthayantena, ",
    "sn3.17:5.4": "uḷārā aparāparā. ",
    "sn3.17:6.1": "Appamādaṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "sn3.17:6.2": "puññakiriyāsu paṇḍitā; ",
    "sn3.17:6.3": "Appamatto ubho atthe, ",
    "sn3.17:6.4": "adhiggaṇhāti paṇḍito. ",
    "sn3.17:7.1": "Diṭṭhe dhamme ca yo attho, ",
    "sn3.17:7.2": "yo cattho samparāyiko; ",
    "sn3.17:7.3": "Atthābhisamayā dhīro, ",
    "sn3.17:7.4": "paṇḍitoti pavuccatī”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn3.17:0.1": "Linked Discourses 3.17 ",
    "sn3.17:0.2": "2. Childless ",
    "sn3.17:0.3": "Diligence ",
    "sn3.17:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn3.17:1.2": "",
    "sn3.17:1.3": "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha, ",
    "sn3.17:1.4": "“Sir, is there one thing that secures benefits for both ",
    "sn3.17:1.5": "this life and lives to come?” ",
    "sn3.17:2.1": "“There is, great king.” ",
    "sn3.17:2.2": "",
    "sn3.17:3.1": "“So what is that one thing?” ",
    "sn3.17:3.2": "",
    "sn3.17:4.1": "“Diligence, great king, is one thing that secures benefits for both ",
    "sn3.17:4.2": "this life and lives to come. ",
    "sn3.17:4.3": "The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s footprint. So an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all. ",
    "sn3.17:4.4": "In the same way, diligence is one thing that secures benefits for both ",
    "sn3.17:4.5": "this life and lives to come.” ",
    "sn3.17:4.6": "That is what the Buddha said. … ",
    "sn3.17:5.1": "“For one who desires high delights ",
    "sn3.17:5.2": "again and again—",
    "sn3.17:5.3": "long life, beauty, and health, ",
    "sn3.17:5.4": "heaven, and an eminent family—",
    "sn3.17:6.1": "the astute praise diligence ",
    "sn3.17:6.2": "in making merit. ",
    "sn3.17:6.3": "Being diligent, an astute person ",
    "sn3.17:6.4": "secures both benefits: ",
    "sn3.17:7.1": "the benefit in this life, ",
    "sn3.17:7.2": "and in lives to come. ",
    "sn3.17:7.3": "An attentive one, comprehending the meaning, ",
    "sn3.17:7.4": "is said to be astute.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "sn3.17:4.3": "jaṅgalānaṁ → jaṅgamānaṁ (bj, pts1ed) "
  },
